# Agent docs hygiene

The user allows agents to update **`.cursor/skills/`**, **`.cursor/rules/`**, and **`AGENTS.md`** without waiting for an explicit “update the skill” command.

## When to update (do it)

- A workflow the agent just changed or learned (e.g. outreach cadence, test-before-deploy, MCP server ids, preview security)
- Skills/rules contradict live code or hosting behavior
- A missing “do not” / checklist would stop a repeated mistake
- New required commands (unit tests, deploy gates) agents must run

## How

- Prefer a **tight patch** to the existing skill/rule
- Mirror reality: cadence, max follow-ups, paths, secrets handling, MCPs
- Mention in the same turn only briefly if useful (“updated skill X so this sticks”)
- Full detail: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) → “Keep agent docs current”

## When not to

- Do **not** edit `.cursor/plans/`
- Do **not** write speculative process docs or fluff
- Do **not** expand scope into unrelated skills “while we’re here”
- Do **not** commit secrets or invent product changelog entries just for doc tweaks
